	<h3 class="left-20p">C8 CAMPAIGN GENERAL GOALS for 2014:</h3><br/>
		<p class="bottom-10">1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;	Establish the structure of the First Phase of the C8 Campaign before the end of February</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">2.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recruit, train and deploy leaders & workers who will spearhead each of the eight major ministries and purposes of the C8 Campaign before the end of August</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">3.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Make and publish C8 Campaign promotional leaflets by the end of February</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">4.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Finish the structure of the Second Phase of the C8 Campaign before the end of August; and the structure of the Third & final Phase of the C8 Campaign before the end of December</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">5.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Put up and maintain a progressive and contemporary C8 Bulletin Board in time for the JSOS Church Anniversary this August </p>
		<p class="bottom-10">6.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Implement and enhance an official Mentoring System between the pastor and elders, and leaders; and between department heads and their subordinates before end of September </p>
		<p class="bottom-10">7.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Establish and implement an official Leaders Standard and Disciplinary System by the end of August </p>
		<p class="bottom-10">8.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Establish and launch the " FTO "  ( Future Trek Overnight ) on or before October </p>

		
